iMedia is evolving to Creative Design

We are designing more than what you think

Check out our new look

Moving forward with the company’s direction to transform experience in customer care. It requires us to extend our design knowledge to learn new skill of UX fundamentals and Front End in building better design solutions. Our goal is to deliver design that is not only visually pleasing but also meet the user needs.

With the new direction, we feel there is a need to make our team’s name more intuitive and self-explanatory that portrays the team expertise. Looking at standard practise in design industry, we decided to make a change to call ourselves “Creative Design Team”. A team that responsible to develop conceptual ideas that convey message by creating aesthetic visuals to deliver mockup, animation, visual design, motion design, design research and usability. Act as a design evangelist, we coordinate design principles and practices inside WDS Company.

Behind The Scene

Madeline Pranatio

Team Lead

With many years of design background, Madeline leads the iMedia team for all the projects from brainstorming to design execution. Not only foresee any issue or problems encountered upon received a project, she is able to identify her team member’s strengths or weakness and encourages them to explore and challenge beyond their limits.

Felix Susanto

Creative Designer

Armed with years of experience in visual creation, Felix demonstrates his ability in multimedia design using a variety of tools. He often draws or creates illustrations during his free time. Felix has a passion in front-end development and meets his newfound love for Bootstrap. His interests motivate him from executing and building prototypes that benefits the project.

Ivy Gue

Creative Designer

Ivy is a multi-disciplinary designer with experience in both print and web. She enjoys exploring different ideas and learning new ways to create solutions with visual impact. Her obsession with designing keeps her motivated (and of course it will have extra boost if there is good food around). You may find her doing her favourite pastime, Cafehopping.
